title: Wan Azizah: If Dr M was so good, he wouldn’t need to meet Anwar
text:
More 
If former prime minister Dr Mahathir Mohamad was so good at uniting the opposition, he wouldn’t need to meet jailed PKR de facto leader Anwar Ibrahim, said PKR president Wan Azizah Wan Ismail. 
“He goes to see Anwar. I think if he is so good at uniting (the opposition), he doesn’t need to come. 
“But he came. There is something that is more than meets the eye,” she told journalists in Subang Jaya today.
